To see this, write for large negative \(x\)

\[
\sqrt{4x^2-1}
=2\,|x|\sqrt{1-\frac1{4x^2}}
=2(-x)\sqrt{1-\frac1{4x^2}}
\quad(x\to-\infty\implies|x|=-x).
\]

Hence

\[
\frac{\sqrt{4x^2-1}}{x+2}
=\frac{-2x\sqrt{1-\frac1{4x^2}}}{x\,(1+\frac2x)}
=-2\;\frac{\sqrt{1-\frac1{4x^2}}}{1+\frac2x}
\;\longrightarrow\;-2\quad(x\to -\infty).
\]

To evaluate 

\[
\lim_{x\to -\infty}\frac{4x}{\sqrt{x^2-1}},
\]

note that for large negative \(x\), \(\sqrt{x^2-1}=\lvert x\rvert\sqrt{1-\tfrac1{x^2}}=-x\,\sqrt{1-\tfrac1{x^2}}\).  Hence

\[
\frac{4x}{\sqrt{x^2-1}}
=\frac{4x}{-x\sqrt{1-\tfrac1{x^2}}}
=\frac{-4}{\sqrt{1-\tfrac1{x^2}}}
\;\xrightarrow[x\to-\infty]{}\;
-4.
\]

Answer: \(\,-4\).
